{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Protect ADHD support and study possible post-COVID impact on diagnoses",
        "additional_details": "Government data shows ADHD diagnoses & referrals have risen sharply in recent years, prompting a national review of assessment pathways & support.\r\nSome independent analyses suggest that ADHD in the UK is historically underdiagnosed, not over.\r\nThere is scientific evidence suggesting COVID can cause long term cognitive & executive function difficulties, which may overlap with or exacerbate ADHD like symptoms. Many people with no prior ADHD diagnosis have reported post infection cognitive changes.",
        "background": "Ensure the current review of rising ADHD, autism and mental health diagnoses explicitly includes examination of the potential impact of post COVID neurological effects, and that all conclusions are based on clinical evidence. Those with ADHD must not lose support due to assumptions of overdiagnosis.",
